  <datafield tag="245" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Improved solid decomposition algorithms for the CAD-to-MC conversion tool McCad</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="260" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="c">2017-03-06</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">• Creating a model for Monte Carlo simulation is a tough task, especially a model with complicate geometry. • McCad supplies a solution to create the model automatically from CAD model. • Two significant functions included by McCad are solid decomposition and void filling. • The former version of McCad is weak in the decomposition function. • New algorithms are applied for improving the stability and efficiency of the decomposition function. • The improved function has been validated with some example models and EU-DEMO model. • The improved McCad could be applied as an efficient modeling tool for Monte Carlo neutronics simulation.</subfield>
